    "text_3": {
      "type": "content-block",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_1": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Retro Revival",
            "tag": "h2",
            "size": "h3",
            "font": "serif"
          }
        },
        "text_1": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Golf fashion is having a nostalgic moment, and the '80s and '90s are making a serious comeback. Varsity sweaters, bold stripes, and vintage-inspired polos are everywhere. It's about channeling that old-school country club vibe, but with fabrics and fits that actually make sense in 2025. Ralph Lauren Golf nails it with throwback polos that feel straight out of a vintage locker room, while Adidas Golf Originals gives the look a streetwear twist. Pair a Ralph Lauren stripe knit with the RLX Tailored Fit Trouser for a refined yet casual vibe, then finish with G/FORE's Gallivanter shoes for the perfect blend of classic and contemporary. Bonus points if you add a cap with a retro logo.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "heading_1",
        "text_1"
      ],
      "settings": {
        "alignment": "left",
        "enable_animation": true
